b'Our latest Cummins-powered Machine of the Month is dedicated to tugboats. Powered by two Cummins QSK95 marine engines with 3,600 BHP each, the tugboats have the necessary power needed to maneuver massive cargo ships around the Takoradi Harbour.  For more information on the tugboats, visit the link in the bio. :ferry: :camera_with_flash: credit: Tor Group \n#cummins #tugboat #tugboats  #maritime'

b'Cummins has a strong marine heritage dating back to the company\xe2\x80\x99s start in 1919. Nowhere is the Cummins marine legacy more apparent than at Bristol Bay, Alaska, where today Cummins powers more than a third of the Bristol Bay fleet. Featured in this video is one such Cummins-powered vessel, the Esa Ruth. Powered by a pair of Cummins QSB 6.7-liter diesel engines, each delivering up to 550 horsepower, the Esa Ruth\xe2\x80\x99s 40-knot speed makes it stand out amongst the crowd of fast boats. In a fishing season of just a few short weeks, when millions of sockeye salmon are making their return to the rivers of Bristol Bay, shaving minutes from your setting or recovery time can make a significant difference to your catch. \nRead about the Esa Ruth by clicking the link in our bio. \n#Cummins #CumminsMarine #bristolbay #sockeyesalmon #alaska'
